@* 
[HCOM-DESIGN NOTE]
Component: ModelCreateUpdateForm.razor

Purpose:
- Renders the editable fields for the Dummy entity.
- Handles validation display only (no CRUD logic, no modal control).

Parameters:
- [Parameter] public Dummy? Dummy { get; set; }
    → Receives the entity instance for form binding.
      In 'create' mode, this is a new Dummy().
      In 'update' mode, this is an existing Dummy with values preloaded.
      Rationale: The form is model-agnostic; it simply binds what it receives.

- [Parameter] public string? Operation { get; set; }
   → Provides context (create/update/read/etc.) for conditional UI or validation behavior.     Important even though form does not perform CRUD itself.

SOC Enforcement:
- Form = View-only logic (fields + validation)
- Index = Controller logic (modal state, CRUD dispatch)
- Modal = Presentation wrapper (UI shell for forms), responsible for form submission.
*@

@using blazor_hcom.Models

@namespace blazor_hcom.Components.Pages.DummyPages

<EditForm EditContext="@EditContext">
	<DataAnnotationsValidator />
	<ValidationSummary class="text-danger" role="alert"/>
	<div class="mb-3">
		<label for="name" class="form-label">Name</label> 
		<InputText id="name" @bind-Value="Dummy!.Name" class="form-control" aria-required="true"/> 
		<ValidationMessage For="() => Dummy.Name" class="text-danger" /> 
	</div>        
	<div class="mb-3">
		<label for="category" class="form-label">Category</label> 
		<InputText id="category" @bind-Value="Dummy!.Category" class="form-control" /> 
		<ValidationMessage For="() => Dummy.Category" class="text-danger" /> 
	</div>        
</EditForm>

@code {
	[Parameter] public Dummy? Dummy { get; set; }
	[Parameter] public string? Operation { get; set; }
	[Parameter] public EditContext? EditContext { get; set; }
}
